options.text: Are you entering the fishing competition?
Sorry, I don't have time now.
Can I buy one of your fishing rods?
I've forgotten how to fish, can you remind me?

350c2772-435e-4607-8363-8d0de59b6684.title: Grandpa Jack
350c2772-435e-4607-8363-8d0de59b6684.text:
Hello!
Come to visit old Grandpa Jack? I can tell ye stories
for sure. I used to be the best fisherman these parts
have seen!

82c40b2e-dbb9-4240-a9e8-b194bbfd28b8.title: Grandpa Jack
82c40b2e-dbb9-4240-a9e8-b194bbfd28b8.text:
Well, when I were a young man we used to take
fishing trips over to Catherby; The fishing over there -
now that was something!

e8f776c1-c588-482a-8744-22e0f3eda319.title: Grandpa Jack
e8f776c1-c588-482a-8744-22e0f3eda319.text:
Anyway, we decided to do a bit of fishing with our nets,
I wasn't having the best of days turning up nothing but
old boots and bits of seaweed. Then my net suddenly
got really heavy!

ffada26d-ba06-497d-933f-a943e92a3ebe.title: Grandpa Jack
ffada26d-ba06-497d-933f-a943e92a3ebe.text: To my amazement I'd caught this little chest thing!

dc7dca94-2d8e-46d2-9d56-6e16a2cdb2fd.title: Grandpa Jack
dc7dca94-2d8e-46d2-9d56-6e16a2cdb2fd.text:
Even more amazing was when I opened it it contained
a diamond the size of a radish! That's the best catch
I've ever had!

bf03f104-ca41-4c4d-99e6-95936884e721.title: <player>
bf03f104-ca41-4c4d-99e6-95936884e721.text: Are you entering the fishing competition?

1e748e73-de3c-4a61-b626-9cb28d644320.title: Grandpa Jack
1e748e73-de3c-4a61-b626-9cb28d644320.text:
I know all about that... I won that four years straight!
I'm too old for that lark now though...

options.text: I don't suppose you could give me any hints?
That's less competition for me then.

e1cb27d4-d463-4855-a14d-a9d953735e02.title: <player>
e1cb27d4-d463-4855-a14d-a9d953735e02.text: Sorry, I don't have time now.

1fce7afe-1cda-40e6-b516-411c15465756.title: Grandpa Jack
1fce7afe-1cda-40e6-b516-411c15465756.text: Young people - always in such a rush.

96f3440a-8e6e-4447-9718-fcc3a9d5fc3d.title: <player>
96f3440a-8e6e-4447-9718-fcc3a9d5fc3d.text: Can I buy one of your fishing rods?

bc7adb10-f5de-44b9-9da8-389a33cdd80a.title: Grandpa Jack
bc7adb10-f5de-44b9-9da8-389a33cdd80a.text:
But young'un, you have your own. I'll not sell you
mine when you already have one!

eef0f3ed-f717-4115-8dcb-18e51a9a3cba.title: Grandpa Jack
eef0f3ed-f717-4115-8dcb-18e51a9a3cba.text:
Of course you can young'un. Let's see now...I think
5 gold is a fair price for a rod which has won the
Fishing contest before eh?

options.text: Very fair, I'll buy that rod!
That's too rich for me, I'll go to Catherby.

e04c5f2d-cd88-47ef-9b50-36ef8ad19eae.title: <player>
e04c5f2d-cd88-47ef-9b50-36ef8ad19eae.text: That's too rich for me, I'll go to Catherby.

2336c2bd-2aaf-40bf-a8c4-0408dfa97498.title: Grandpa Jack
2336c2bd-2aaf-40bf-a8c4-0408dfa97498.text:
If you're sure.... passing up an opportunity of a lifetime
you are.

298f1b75-9aff-4369-8432-e0bb0b2a4298.title: <player>
298f1b75-9aff-4369-8432-e0bb0b2a4298.text: Very fair, I'll buy that rod!

6b3db7b7-4e0d-4088-9c42-b86913ae9362.text: You hand over the money and receive a fishing rod.

3b99db58-3620-4d83-a217-61b300dadc76.title: <player>
3b99db58-3620-4d83-a217-61b300dadc76.text: I've forgotten how to fish, can you remind me?

b5b5b19d-cdaf-4d7e-9b42-43a396305fef.title: Grandpa Jack
b5b5b19d-cdaf-4d7e-9b42-43a396305fef.text:
Of course! Let me see now...You'll need a rod and bait.
You can fish with a net too, but not in the competition.

82694253-c623-4bea-a19d-10aa0d4536fb.title: <player>
82694253-c623-4bea-a19d-10aa0d4536fb.text: Ok... I think I can get those at Catherby.

b86df0ac-b3df-429a-ad49-1c7708961046.title: Grandpa Jack
b86df0ac-b3df-429a-ad49-1c7708961046.text:
Then simply find yourself a fishing spot, either in the
competition near here, or wherever you can - I
recommend net fishing in Catherby. Net or Lure the
fish in the fishing spot by clicking on it and then be

f14a69c3-0db8-4e2b-811c-64e015f5f642.title: <player>
f14a69c3-0db8-4e2b-811c-64e015f5f642.text: That's less competition for me then.

d5823a57-d9af-4ecc-adc8-9270ad852e70.title: Grandpa Jack
d5823a57-d9af-4ecc-adc8-9270ad852e70.text:
Why you young whippersnapper! If I was twenty years
ounger I'd show you something that's for sure!

8662098f-91d7-4133-b055-9a9eef1d2d52.title: <player>
8662098f-91d7-4133-b055-9a9eef1d2d52.text: I don't suppose you could give me any hints?

01ac02da-32b7-4e38-a4e9-69e6419437cc.title: Grandpa Jack
01ac02da-32b7-4e38-a4e9-69e6419437cc.text:
Well, you sometimes get these really big fish in the
water just by the outflow pipes.

6d336e28-bd11-4571-8508-8e39d21f4037.title: Grandpa Jack
6d336e28-bd11-4571-8508-8e39d21f4037.text: I think they're some kind of carp...

f147f404-7d8b-4fc4-9e63-b96abd2b94ae.title: Grandpa Jack
f147f404-7d8b-4fc4-9e63-b96abd2b94ae.text:
Try to get a spot round there. The best sort of bait
for them is red vine worms.

c9f0146f-41b4-4665-9cc0-4821d597b464.title: Grandpa Jack
c9f0146f-41b4-4665-9cc0-4821d597b464.text:
I used to get those from McGrubor's wood, north of
here. Just dig around in the red vines up there but be
careful of the guard dogs.

50d7dc69-8320-4230-81af-3cc6bec27a2f.title: Grandpa Jack
50d7dc69-8320-4230-81af-3cc6bec27a2f.text:
There's this weird creepy guy who says he's not a
vampyre using that spot. He keeps winning too.

d8346c34-0c0c-40dc-bd81-d9454ca6dbce.title: Grandpa Jack
d8346c34-0c0c-40dc-bd81-d9454ca6dbce.text:
Ahh well, I'm sure you'll find something to put him off.
After all, there must be a kitchen around here with
some garlic in it, perhaps in Seers Village or Ardougne.
If he's pretending to be a vampyre then he can pretend
